{
  "texts": [
    "For example, the possibility of ubiquitous personalization of AI content, in which all media consumed by everyone on earth-every book, every movie, every game, every educational worksheet-has been precisely tailored to that individual's unique and evolving preferences, paves the way for vastly greater emissions footprints for future AI systems.",
    "Whether the net effect of increasingly efficient algorithms and larger training sets and deployment contexts will cause total energy use to increase or decrease over time remains to be seen.",
    "Similarly, societal changes regarding the footprint of various human societies may also change the ratio between AI and human activity.",
    "For example, the per capita impact of a human in the US has been mostly falling since it peaked in the 1970s 22, and the per capita impact of a human in India has been rising almost continuously since the 1940s 22 (although the impact of a resident of India is still only one seventh the impact of a US resident).",
    "These trends may continue, or may be altered by social and/or technical changes."
  ]
}